  "CEILING": "mRNA HLA != surface MHC-I protein; scRNA DROPOUT inflates the HLA-low fraction (headline is an UPPER BOUND -> conservatively OVER-estimates toxicity); HLA-I is IFN-gamma inducible (resting atlas may understate induced levels); scRNA resolves the HLA-A GENE not the A*02 ALLELE. Worst-donor (never pooled), per RUNG-5/6.",
  "INTERPRETATION": "This replaces RUNG-7's assumed 5% normal HLA-low fraction with a measured, per-vital-tissue number. The worst vital type sets the gate's off-tumour-toxicity floor (data_grounded_FPR). If the measured HLA-low fraction is well below 5%, the blocker is more reliable than assumed (good); if higher, RUNG-7's safety was optimistic and the gate is more toxic than modelled."
